                <h5>White Sapphire</h5>
                <p>Like diamonds, white sapphire is available in both natural and lab-grown varieties. Natural white sapphires can have a milky appearance, while lab-grown varieties are a bit clearer, which makes them a better alternative for diamonds. These stones are definitely durable but they’re not as brilliant as diamonds as they don’t have the same kind of sparkle.</p>
                <h5>The Lab-Grown Advantage</h5>
                <p>Diamond simulants became popular solely because of the high cost attached to mined diamonds. With the introduction of lab-grown diamonds, however, this has changed. <strong>Lab-grown diamonds </strong>are better than every diamond alternative available as they are <strong>100% real diamonds</strong>  and have all the same qualities that make mined diamonds one of the most sought-after stones in the world.</p>
                <p>Lab-grown diamonds allow you to enjoy the best of both worlds. You get a real diamond, one of the most precious stones known to man, that is affordable and ethical!</p>
